  "prompt": "How would you know that a guy has a crush on you or likes you even though if you are friends?",
  "response": "It can sometimes be tricky to discern whether a friend has a romantic interest in you, but there are several signs that might indicate a crush. Here are some common indicators:\n\n1. **Increased Attention**: If he goes out of his way to spend time with you or seems to prioritize you over others, it might be a sign of affection.\n\n2. **Flirty Behavior**: Look for signs of flirting, such as teasing, playful banter, or compliments that seem more personal than usual.\n\n3. **Body Language**: Pay attention to his body language. Signs like maintaining eye contact, leaning in when talking to you, or finding excuses for physical contact can indicate feelings beyond friendship.\n\n4. **Interest in Your Life**: If he asks detailed questions about your life, thoughts, and feelings, and remembers the little things you say, it might indicate he cares more deeply.\n\n5. **Nervousness or Shyness**: He may appear nervous or shy around you compared to how he acts with other friends. This can include fidgeting, blushing, or avoiding direct eye contact.\n\n6. **Jealousy**: If he seems a bit jealous when you talk about other guys or spend time with other friends, it could be a sign that he has deeper feelings.\n\n7. **Frequent Communication**: If he texts or calls you frequently, even without a specific reason, it might indicate that he enjoys your company and wants to connect more.\n\n8. **Longer Conversations**: If conversations tend to go deep and last longer than they do with other friends, he may be looking to build a stronger connection with you.\n\n9. **Physical Proximity**: He might try to sit closer to you or find excuses to be near you in social settings.\n\n10. **Reactions to Your Relationships**: How he reacts when you mention dating others or when you're with someone else can be revealing. Positive support or disappointment may suggest he has feelings for you.\n\nRemember that these signs may not guarantee that someone has a crush on you, as individual behaviors can vary widely. The best way to clarify feelings is through open and honest communication, either by discussing it directly or suggesting a casual hangout that could allow for a more profound connection.",
